The paper discusses methods for evaluating the impact of journals in a specific subject category, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories related to information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), cryptography (cs.CR), and computational geometry (cs.CY). However, given that the study focuses on citation distributions and bias factors, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
